  "chapter": {
    "number": 4,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "Punishment Brings No Repentance"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Hear this word,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "you cows of Bashan on Mount Samaria,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "you women who oppress the poor",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and crush the needy,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who say to your husbands,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "“Bring us more to drink.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          "The Lord GOD has sworn by His holiness:",
          {
            "lineBreak": true
          },
          {
            "text": "“Behold, the days are coming",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when you will be taken away with hooks,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and your posterity with fishhooks.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "You will go out through broken walls,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "each one straight ahead of her,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and you will be cast out toward Harmon,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 1306
          },
          {
            "text": "”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "declares the LORD."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Go to Bethel and transgress;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "rebel even more at Gilgal!",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "Bring your sacrifices every morning,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "your tithes every three days.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 1307
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Offer leavened bread as a thank offering,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and loudly proclaim your freewill offerings.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "For that is what you children of Israel love to do,”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "declares the Lord GOD."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“I beset all your cities with cleanness of teeth",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 1308
          },
          {
            "text": "and all your towns with lack of bread,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "yet you did not return to Me,”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "declares the LORD."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“I also withheld the rain from you",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "when the harvest was three months away.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I sent rain on one city",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but withheld it from another.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "One field received rain;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "another without rain withered.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "People staggered from city to city",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "for water to drink,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "but they were not satisfied;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "yet you did not return to Me,”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "declares the LORD."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“I struck you with blight and mildew",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "in your growing gardens and vineyards;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the locust devoured your fig and olive trees,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "yet you did not return to Me,”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "declares the LORD."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“I sent plagues among you",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "like those of Egypt;",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I killed your young men with the sword,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "along with your captured horses.",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "I filled your nostrils with the stench of your camp,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "yet you did not return to Me,”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "declares the LORD."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Some of you I overthrew",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as I overthrew Sodom and Gomorrah,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and you were like a firebrand",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 1309
          },
          {
            "text": "snatched from a blaze,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "yet you did not return to Me,”",
            "poem": 2
          },
          "declares the LORD."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "“Therefore, that is what I will do",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "to you, O Israel,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and since I will do this to you,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "prepare to meet your God, O Israel!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "For behold, He who forms the mountains,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "who creates the wind",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "and reveals His thoughts to man,",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "who turns the dawn to darkness",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and strides on the heights of the earth—",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "text": "the LORD, the God of Hosts, is His name.”",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
      {
        "noteId": 1306,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "That is, possibly Mount Hermon",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 4,
          "verse": 3
        }
      },
      {
        "noteId": 1307,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "Or years",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 4,
          "verse": 4
        }
      },
      {
        "noteId": 1308,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "That is, with empty stomachs",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 4,
          "verse": 6
        }
      },
      {
        "noteId": 1309,
        "caller": "+",
        "text": "That is, a burning stick",
        "reference": {
          "chapter": 4,
          "verse": 11
        }
      }
    ]
  },
